<cb:div type="taisho-notes">
<head>大正 校勘記</head>
<p>
<note n="0104001" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104001">〔有〕－【石】</note>
<note n="0104002" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104002">〔未來世〕－【石】</note>
<note n="0104003" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104003">〔及離繫〕－【石】</note>
<note n="0104004" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104004">耶＝邪【石】下同</note>
<note n="0104005" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104005">過＝現【宮】</note>
<note n="0104006" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104006">Bhāva.</note>
<note n="0104007" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104007">體＝顯【三】【宮】【石】</note>
<note n="0104008" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104008">Avasthā.</note>
<note n="0104009" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0104009">來＝（來）【石】</note>
<note n="0105001" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105001">Phala-dāna-pratigraha.</note>
<note n="0105002" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105002">因＝同【三】【宮】</note>
<note n="0105003" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105003">Kāritra.</note>
<note n="0105004" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105004">〔起〕－【石】</note>
<note n="0105005" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105005">謂＝誰【三】【宮】</note>
<note n="0105006" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105006">許＋（不許）【石】</note>
<note n="0105007" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105007">Sarvadā asti.</note>
<note n="0105008" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105008">Laguḍa-śīkhīyaka.</note>
<note n="0105009" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105009">Ājīvika.</note>
<note n="0105010" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0105010">位＝住【三】【宮】</note>
<note n="0106001" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0106001">由＋（獲勝我暮）【石】</note>
<note n="0106002" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0106002">彼＝破【三】【宮】，破我品 Ātmavāda-pratiṣedha.</note>
<note n="0106003" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0106003">雨＝兩【三】【宮】</note>
<note n="0106004" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0106004">〔十六種法為〕－【石】</note>
<note n="0106005" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0106005">應＋（應）【宋】【元】【宮】</note>
<note n="0107001" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107001">〔隨眠〕－【石】</note>
<note n="0107002" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107002">於＝謂【三】【宮】【石】</note>
<note n="0107003" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107003">眠＝增【宮】</note>
<note n="0107004" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107004">身＝見【明】</note>
<note n="0107005" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107005">恃＝情【三】【宮】</note>
<note n="0107006" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107006"><g ref="#CB00654">𣣋</g>＝凌【三】【宮】【石】</note>
<note n="0107007" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107007">謂＝前【宋】【元】</note>
<note n="0107008" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107008">或流布本作惑</note>
<note n="0107009" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107009">瀑＝暴【三】【宮】下同</note>
<note n="0107010" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107010">流＋（四無明瀑流）【石】</note>
<note n="0107011" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107011">Paryavasthāna.</note>
<note n="0107012" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107012">說＝欲【三】【宮】</note>
<note n="0107013" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107013">Bhavāsrava.</note>
<note n="0107014" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107014">唯＝准【明】【宮】</note>
<note n="0107015" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107015">Kāmaugha.</note>
<note n="0107016" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107016">Kāmayoga.</note>
<note n="0107017" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107017">獨＝猛【三】【宮】</note>
<note n="0107018" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107018">纏＝種【三】【宮】【石】</note>
<note n="0107019" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0107019">無明＋（瀑流謂三界無明）【石】</note>
<note n="0108001" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0108001">〔家〕－【石】</note>
<note n="0108002" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0108002">為＋（生）【三】【宮】</note>
<note n="0108003" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0108003">〔欲欲〕－【石】</note>
<note n="0108004" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0108004">謂＝諸【宋】【元】【宮】</note>
<note n="0108005" resp="#resp1" place="foot text" type="orig" target="#nkr_note_orig_0108005">漂＋（漂）【石】</note>
</p>
